        "url": "about/design/",
        "content": "Design \u00b6 Guild Role Define the brand identity of the project and develop a comprehensive design system. Create material for daily use both at marketing and product level. Research and develop pieces with clean, functional design and community feedback. Generate private and open source tools for the community. Methodology \u00b6 Our design vision is centered in two elements: 1. Structural organization Design language Creating an easy to use comprehensive design system that can be accessed in our Figma organization and establishing design protocols and principles to follow. Having a shared understanding in communication between teams. Cultivate psychological safety Creating a safe space for discussion and tools for knowledge about mindfulness, design + growing business. Foster innovation in the creative process Oftentimes in this industry people force creativity to align to schedules, when in reality it's a process of inspiration that's unable to be constrained into boxes. We want to foster that type of creativity even in a fast-paced environment. Making time to have the freedom of exploration and then having the ability to organize thoughts and document them will make us a stronger, more innovative team. 2.  User centric community Accessibility Making sure our product is accessible to people with disabilities. Incorporating that into our core mission and hearing their needs. User centric imagery Infographics. Motion graphics Mixed content (video+data) Instructions/manuals/guides Global design We want to share with people and participate in the global design community as a project. Reserve designs in an open and transparent way, providing knowledge,  fighting desinformation and sharing content as templates, tips, tutorials. Security We want users to feel secure about our products and services. Principles of this guild \u00b6 7 basic principles of universal design Equality of use: Design should be easy to use and suitable for everyone, regardless of their abilities and skills. Flexibility Simple and functional use Understandable information Error tolerance Low physical effort Space and size for approach and use",
